# Billing Standards

## PaymentProvider interface — NUNCA acoplar ao Stripe/Pague.dev diretamente
```typescript
// packages/shared/src/providers/payment.provider.ts
export interface PaymentProvider {
  createCustomer(userId: string, email: string): Promise<string>;
  createSubscription(customerId: string, quantity: number): Promise<{
    subscriptionId: string;
    status: SubscriptionStatus;
    currentPeriodEnd: Date;
  }>;
  updateQuantity(subscriptionId: string, quantity: number): Promise<void>;
  cancelSubscription(subscriptionId: string, atPeriodEnd: boolean): Promise<void>;
  handleWebhook(rawBody: Buffer, signature: string): Promise<BillingWebhookEvent>;
}

// NoOp para OSS / desenvolvimento
export class NoOpPaymentProvider implements PaymentProvider {
  async createCustomer() { return 'noop_customer'; }
  async createSubscription() { return { subscriptionId: 'noop', status: 'ACTIVE', currentPeriodEnd: new Date(9999, 0) }; }
  async updateQuantity() {}
  async cancelSubscription() {}
  async handleWebhook() { throw new Error('No billing in OSS mode'); }
}
```

## Webhook handler — verificação HMAC obrigatória
```typescript
// apps/api/app/api/webhooks/stripe/route.ts
export async function POST(req: NextRequest) {
  const rawBody = await req.arrayBuffer();
  const signature = req.headers.get('stripe-signature') ?? '';

  let event: BillingWebhookEvent;
  try {
    event = await paymentProvider.handleWebhook(Buffer.from(rawBody), signature);
  } catch {
    return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Invalid signature' }, { status: 400 });
  }

  // Idempotência: checar se evento já processado
  const processed = await redis.get(`webhook:processed:${event.id}`);
  if (processed) return NextResponse.json({ ok: true });

  await processWebhookEvent(event);
  await redis.set(`webhook:processed:${event.id}`, '1', 'EX', 86400); // 24h TTL

  return NextResponse.json({ ok: true });
}
```

## Sync de quantidade de números
- Trigado em: add number, remove number, toggle monitored
- Trigado em: background job diário (reconciliação)
- NUNCA confiar apenas no contador — sempre recalcular com COUNT query
- Após sync: chamar paymentProvider.updateQuantity() se CLOUD_BILLING=true

## Grace period
- PAST_DUE: monitoramento continua por 7 dias
- UNPAID após grace: pausar novos health checks, preservar dados históricos
- CANCELED: monitoramento continua até currentPeriodEnd
